English [ edit ]
Etymology [ edit ]

From stress +‎ -or .
Noun [ edit ]

stressor ( plural stressors )

    ( psychology , biology ) An environmental condition or influence that stresses (i.e. causes stress for) an organism. quotations ▼

Derived terms [ edit ]

    technostressor 

